[normal]1.1
[normal]              
[normal]My name is Peter Martin, a private resident in the UK.
[normal]1.2
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]I submit evidence because I believe the BBC as it stands in word and deed no longer represents me or my family, our wishes or the best interests of the country whose name it 
[normal]bears.
[normal]1.3
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]I can see no justification for their ‘unique’ funding to be compelled by a tax on the population for watching broadcast content live, and certainly not (as some suggest) in future for possessing the means to receive web-based content by any means. I
[normal]t is an anachronism in the global village of 2013 and beyond.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]2.1 I seek to address two main questions listed from the committee document, as all others become rendered redundant if the answers to these are proven to be negative:
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]* 
[normal]              
[normal]How well has the BBC performed in the current Charter period in achieving its mission and public purposes?
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]* 
[normal]              
[normal]How should the BBC be governed, regulated and held accountable beyond 2016?
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]2.2 BBC Charters and guidelines and fancy mission statements aside,
[normal] simply put, I would like the committee to shine a spotlight on whether the BBC has, is and can in future deliver a professional, accurate broadcast product based on objectivity and integrity.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]2.3 And does the BBC have regulatory mechanisms in place that 
[normal]are transparent, fair, responsive and effective to keep it that way?
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]Yes... or no?
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]2.4 If no, and examples to follow will provide substantive evidence of this, funding or governance, remits, representations, promotions, etc are moot.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]2.5 If a national b
[normal]roadcast media monopoly can't be accurate or trustworthy, it has no business being in business.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]Especially by state-enforced, compelled funding means.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]2.6 Hence I propose to illustrate failures of purported mission during Charter period, and in complemen
[normal]t worse failures in oversight as follows:
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]Appreciating that individual complaints can and will not be entertained, nonetheless my (vastly documented) 
[normal]personal experiences with the latter do have a bearing and will be mentioned (evidence available).
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]The abuses are egregious and go to the core of all the BBC needs, at last, with luck via this committee, to be held to account for properly.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]3. Mission Cre[bold]ep &amp; Failure[bold]&#xa0;
[normal]3.1 There seems of late a plethora of inquiries, reviews &amp; consultations &amp; surveys regarding the BBC, from inside to out.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]In short order we have had Pollard (as will be discussed later, one must wonder what its £3M tag was that worth?) 
[normal]http://bl
[normal]o
