[normal]sible and they are now elsewhere’ without a wee bit more probing?
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]In a world now no longer as sanguine about rewards for failure, it is one thing to bribe the less able to take the heave-ho, but delving into those deep, uniquely-funded pockets to remove a
[normal] bully, on top of their avoiding censure or publicity not always accorded the rest of the non-gilded classes, seems… very generous. 
